15 1 1 Pilot in deadly crash had no eerience landing in San Francisco  CNNcom
15 1 2 San Francisco [Breaking news update at : pm]
15 1 3 The pilot of the Asiana Airlines plane that crashed in San Francisco on Saturday was making his first landing with a Boeing at San Francisco International Airport the airline said
15 1 4 But it wasnt his first time flying to San Francisco
15 1 5 The pilot Lee Kanggook had flown from Seoul to the city several times between and  the airline said
15 1 6 He has also clocked hours flying a Boeing 
15 1 7 [Previous story updated at : pm ET]
15 1 8 NTSB: Pilots attempted to abort landing seconds before impact
15 1 9 The cockpit voice recorder of Asiana Airlines Flight appears to show the pilots tried to abort the landing less than two seconds before the plane crashed on the runway at San Francisco International Airport the head of the National Transportation Safety Board said Sunday
15 1 10 The planes voice and flight data recorders show that the flight from South Korea was coming in too slow and too low and that the pilots appear to have increased speed seven seconds before impact Deborah Hersman said
15 1 11 A stall warning sounded four seconds before the crash and the crew then made an internal decision to initiate a goaround seconds to impact she said
15 1 12 The NTSBs preliminary assessment of the planes cockpit and flight data recorders appear to indicate that the flight went from a routine landing to a disaster in a matter of seconds
15 1 13 But when asked if pilot error was to blame Hersman said the crash landing was still under investigation
15 1 14 I would discourage anyone from drawing any conclusions at this point she said adding that investigators are still working to corroborate the information on the recorders
15 1 15 But what happened inside the cockpit of the Boeing may well be the key factor in Saturdays accident that killed two people injured and forced the temporary closure of one of the countrys largest airports
15 1 16 Amateur video obtained exclusively by CNN on Sunday shows the plane approaching the runway and striking what appears to be a seawall before spinning counterclockwise and coming to a stop
15 1 17 Fred Hayes said he shot the video about a mile from the crash scene
15 1 18 Related: Asiana Airlines crash: At a glance
15 1 19 Some of the answers to what happened may just hinge on what investigators found on the voice and flight data recorders
15 1 20 What we need to do is corroborate the information we have both on the flight data recorder and the cockpit voice recorder Hersman said
15 1 21 But Ill tell you some of the things we are seeing on the flight data recorder are mirroring some of the things that are going on on the cockpit voice recorder
15 1 22 For example she said the increase of power in the engines appears to correlate with the cockpit crews internal decision to do a goaround a call to abort the landing and try it again
15 1 23 Asiana Flight  with passengers and crew members was at the end of a more than hour direct flight from Seoul South Korea when it began its descent
15 1 24 According to the recorders the flights approach appeared normal as the descended and there is no discussion of aircraft approach among the crew
15 1 25 The target air speed for the approach of the flight was knots and the crew can be heard on the cockpit voice recorder acknowledging the speed Hersman said
15 1 26 But the speed was significantly below knots and we are not talking about a few knots she said
15 1 27 At about four seconds before the plane crash landed the pilots received an aural and physical warning inside the cockpit that the plane was on the verge of an aerodynamic stall meaning it was about to lose its ability to stay in the air
15 1 28 The warning  known as a stick shaker  included a verbal warning the plane that was flying too low and a physical warning when the throttle shook
15 1 29 South Korean and NTSB investigators will jointly question Lee Kanggook the pilot who was sitting in the captains seat of Asiana Flight  on Monday Choi Jeongho the head of South Koreans Aviation Policy Bureau said
15 1 30 Lee had hours of eerience flying the B he said
15 1 31 They will also question Lee Jeongmin who was sitting in the copilots seat Choi said
15 1 32 Asiana CEO and President Yoon Youngdoo has said there was no engine failure to his knowledge
15 1 33 South Korean investigators will work alongside US investigators
15 1 34 The NTSB has ruled out weather as a problem and said that conditions were right for a visual landing
15 1 35 But investigators are looking into whether construction at the airport may have played a role
15 1 36 Construction to extend a runway safety area temporarily shut off the socalled glide slope system which is one of several options pilots have to help them land planes safely Hersman said
15 1 37 Internal damage to the plane is really striking she said and officials are thankful there werent more deaths
15 1 38 Survivors of the crash were being treated Sunday for injuries ranging from paralysis to severe road rash
15 1 39 In all people were hospitalized and others walked away from the crash landing
15 1 40 The number who emerged unscathed prompted the citys fire chief to describe it as nothing short of a miracle
15 1 41 On the runway medics found the bodies of the two teen girls lying next to burning wreckage
15 1 42 They were identified by Asiana Airlines as Ye Mengyuan and Wang Linjia both Chinese nationals
15 1 43 We were eecting a lot of burns said Dr Margaret Knudson San Francisco General Hospitals chief of surgery
15 1 44 But we didnt see them
15 1 45 At San Francisco General survivors remained hospitalized six of them in critical condition
15 1 46 Related: Passengers knew they were too low
15 1 47 Many of the injured said they were sitting toward the rear of the aircraft said Knudson
15 1 48 Several suffered abdominal injuries and spine fractures some of which include paralysis and head trauma she said
15 1 49 Many patients also were treated for severe road rash which suggests that they were dragged Knudson said
15 1 50 The conditions of victims at other hospitals were not made public Sunday
15 1 51 Survivors and witnesses reported the yearold airliner appeared to be flying too low as it approached the end of a runway near the bay
15 1 52 Eert: The plane should never have been close to the seawall
15 1 53 Airport technology called the Instrument Landing System or ILS  which normally would help pilots correctly approach the runway  was not operating at the time according to a Federal Aviation Administration bulletin
15 1 54 The ILS integrates with the aircrafts cockpit to trigger an audible warning consultant and retired pilot Mark Weiss told CNN You hear a mechanical voice that says too low too low too low
15 1 55 The ILS is nice to have Weiss said but its not critical on the 
15 1 56 There are redundant systems aboard the aircraft that would provide similar warnings if the plane was coming in too low said Weiss who has landed s hundreds of times
15 1 57 The pilot operating the aircraft was a veteran who had been flying for Asiana since  the airline said
15 1 58 Witnesses recount the crash
15 1 59 Survivors reported hearing no warning from the cockpit before the landing
15 1 60 Passengers scrambled to exit a crash scene that one survivor described as surreal
15 1 61 When rescuers arrived they found some passengers coming out of the water said city fire chief Joanne HayesWhite
15 1 62 There was a fire on the plane so the assumption might be that they went near the waters edge which is very shallow to maybe douse themselves with water she said
15 1 63 Related: Why the crash was survivable
15 1 64 Some jumped out or slid down emergency chutes with luggage in hand
15 1 65 Statistically was the safest year in terms of aviation accidents worldwide since  according to the Aviation Safety Network
15 1 66 Data show that there were fatal airliner accidents which caused deaths according to ASN stats
15 1 67 Thats well below the year annual average of accidents and fatalities
15 1 68 Survival rates have improved due to better staff training and safety advances during the s and s according to the group
15 1 69 Asianas flight history over last years
15 1 70 CNNs Faith Karimi Dana Ford Thom Patterson and Aaron Cooper contributed to this report

16 1 1 Passengers begin legal action against Boeing after Asiana crash  CNNcom
16 1 2 Passengers who were aboard Asiana Airlines Flight  which crashed in San Francisco began legal action against Boeing Co which made the plane according to a law firm representing passengers
16 1 3 Boeing which is headquartered in Chicago declined comment
16 1 4 Spokeswoman Debbie Heathers referred all calls to the National Transportation Safety Board
16 1 5 Ribbeck Law Chartered a Chicagobased law firm said Tuesday that it had filed the initial court petition on behalf of more than passengers
16 1 6 The firm said Asiana Airlines will be added as a defendant in the next few days
16 1 7 Legal action will also be taken against several unidentified component part manufacturers who may be responsible for this disaster the firm said in a statement
16 1 8 Asiana spokesman Ki Won Suh declined to comment on the law firms plans against the airline
16 1 9 The Asiana fell short of its approach and crashed on the runway at San Francisco airport on July 
16 1 10 Three people were killed and more than others hurt
16 1 11 Seconds before crash passengers knew they were too low
16 1 12 The NTSB is investigating
16 1 13 The early stage of the investigation has focused heavily on actions of the crew during the landing attempt
16 1 14 The law firm filed a petition for discovery in Cook County Circuit Court in Illinois and the petition demands that the court orders the defendants to immediately release to the victims of the crash all relevant evidence concerning design and manufacturing records of the accident aircraft as well as any records concerning its maintenance the law firm said in a statement
16 1 15 The passengers represented by the firm include some who have serious back injuries broken legs and brain trauma said attorney Monica R Kelly
16 1 16 During the crash sliding ramps deployed inside the plane blocking passengers access to the exit door and trapping them inside the burning plane the law firm alleged
16 1 17 Also passengers were injured when seats collapsed during the crashlanding Kelly said
16 1 18 The law firm also cites reports that the crash could have been caused by a mechanical malfunction of the autothrottle according to the firms statement
16 1 19 Related: Asiana to proceed with TV station suit
16 1 20 CNNs Kyung Lah contributed to this report

17 1 1 rd person dies from Asiana crash hospital says  CNNcom
17 1 2 A third person identified as a minor girl died from injuries suffered in the Asiana Airlines crash last week hospital officials said
17 1 3 She had been in critical condition at the Bay Area hospital since the July crash San Francisco General spokeswoman Rachael Kagan said
17 1 4 The hospital didnt release any additional information about her  including her name age or ethnicity  in keeping with her parents wishes
17 1 5 Its a very very sad day today at San Francisco General Hospital said Dr Geoffrey Manley chief of neurosurgery
17 1 6 We have all done everything we could
17 1 7 QA: How does an air crash investigation work?
17 1 8 Two others  both yearold girls from China  were reported dead soon after the Boeing crashlanded at San Francisco International Airport
17 1 9 One of those teenagers was hit on the runway by a fire truck though its unclear whether she was already dead when she was struck San Francisco police spokesman Albie Esparza said
17 1 10 At the time firefighters were using flame retardant that ended up surrounding areas immediately around the plane with foam Esparza said
17 1 11 When the truck repositioned itself to get a better aim of the fuselage they discovered the body of the victim in the fresh track from the path of the truck he added
17 1 12 The foam was thick enough to cover a body Esparza noted
17 1 13 Moreover it is difficult for those in the industrialsize fire trucks that responded to crash to see things on the ground the police spokesman said
17 1 14 Right now we are waiting results from the coroner to determine if she died from the crash or the fire engine going over her the police spokesman said
17 1 15 And that will be part of our investigations like any other case by our hitandrun and major accidents investigations teams
17 1 16 Of the passengers and crew on board people survived  of whom walked away relatively unscathed
17 1 17 The others were sent to hospitals
17 1 18 Opinion: Our terror over flying has cost us
17 1 19 A handful of them remained hospitalized including six patients at San Francisco General
17 1 20 That hospitals figure includes two adults in critical condition with spinal cord injuries abdominal injuries internal bleeding road rash and fractures
17 1 21 San Francisco International Airport is also working to get back to normal
17 1 22 The planes fuselage was hauled away on flatbed trucks Friday to a remote section of the airport San Francisco International Airport said in a news release
17 1 23 On Friday a Southwest Airlines jet landed on the runway where the crash occurred  signifying that for the first time in six days all four of the airports runways were operational
17 1 24 The tremendous efforts and aroundtheclock work of airport staff government agencies airline tenants and contractors allowed us to complete all repairs and safety certifications for Runway L in a timely and efficient manner airport director John L Martin said
17 1 25 While the wreckage has been hauled away investigators still have not pinpointed exactly why Flight crashed or who was to blame
17 1 26 Did Asiana pilot have enough eerience?
17 1 27 An indepth review of the cockpit voice recorder shows two pilots called for the landing to be aborted before the plane hit a seawall and crashed onto the runway the head of the National Transportation Safety Board said
17 1 28 The first internal call by one of the three pilots in the cockpit to abort the landing came three seconds before the crash
17 1 29 A second call was made by another pilot seconds before impact NTSB chief Deborah Hersman said
17 1 30 The agency has begun wrapping up its investigation at the airport and crews are cleaning up the debris left by the crash
17 1 31 Investigators turned the runway back over to the airport
17 1 32 CNNs Chelsea J Carter Augie Martin and Ed Payne contributed to this report

18 1 1 NTSB: Asiana jet pilot was halfway through training to fly Boeing  CNNcom
18 1 2 The pilot at the helm of Asiana Airlines Flight was training to fly a Boeing and was sitting next to a man in his first trip as an instructor pilot when their planes main landing gear hit a seawall around San Franciscos airport a US official said Tuesday
18 1 3 Deborah Hersman the head of the National Transportation Safety Board revealed these and other details during a news conference that included information about the pilots and their flying eerience based on the interviews theyve conducted with investigators
18 1 4 Having finished classroom and simulator training the flying pilot  as Hersman referred to him  was in the piloting portion of his training to fly a Boeing at the time of Saturdays crash
18 1 5 He had flown legs and had about hours of flying time with the  which put him about halfway through the training required by Asiana of legs and flight hours when the plane went down Hersman said
18 1 6 Did pilot have enough eerience?
18 1 7 Sitting beside him during Saturdays flight from Seoul to San Francisco was the instructor pilot
18 1 8 The trip across the Pacific was the first time he had been an instructor pilot and the first time hed traveled with the flying pilot according to Hersman
18 1 9 That seemingly uneventful more than hour flight ended in a few chaotic panicked minutes of fury after which two people were dead and others were transported to local hospitals
18 1 10 Sections of the cabin  are found very early in the debris field said Hersman who had walked a few hundred feet from the seawall where the planes landing gear and then tail first slammed into the seawall to where it mercifully came to a rest
18 1 11 You can see aircraft parts gallery materials newspapers magazines and flooring
18 1 12 According to the pilots accounts the tensions started before the plane touched ground
18 1 13 The three pilots in the cockpit  another was in the cabin  told investigators they set the auto throttle speed to knots  mph which is the speed it should have been going
18 1 14 Akin to cruise control auto throttles are used to maintain a planes speed
18 1 15 At feet above ground the instructor pilot said he noted precision approach path indicator lights indicated the giant jet was too low
18 1 16 It was then he recognized that the auto throttles were not maintaining speed and he established a goaround attitude said the NTSB chief
18 1 17 He went to push the throttles forward but he stated that the other pilot had already done so
18 1 18 Hersman cautioned anyone from jumping to conclusions as to whether a mechanical or pilot error is to blame for the crash
18 1 19 She also spoke specifically about the auto throttles saying investigators were delving into how they were working and how they were used
18 1 20 But Hersman also stated: The crew is required to maintain a safe aircraft  One of the very critical things that needs to be monitored on an approach to landing is speed
18 1 21 So we need to understand what was going on in the cockpit and also what was going on in the aircraft
18 1 22 dead injured  including ejected flight attendants
18 1 23 When it departed South Korea Flight had passengers and crew aboard
18 1 24 Despite the scale of the wreckage  a hole burned through much of the cabins roof and the aircrafts back half lopped off  walked away
18 1 25 Others werent so lucky most of all the two Chinese teenagers who died in the crash
18 1 26 Girls killed in crash were headed for camp
18 1 27 Those working on the flight were among the injured
18 1 28 The third pilot in the cockpit cracked a rib
18 1 29 One flight attendant was temporarily trapped by an evacuation chute that opened inside the plane
18 1 30 Two other flight attendants were not in their seats at the rear of the aircraft when the plane finally ground to a halt because they were ejected as the aircraft broke up
18 1 31 They were found down the runway and off to the side of the runway Hersman said
18 1 32 Flight attendants hailed as heroes
18 1 33 Many of those hospitalized have been released
18 1 34 At San Francisco General Hospital for instance of the patients are now free to go home
18 1 35 But others still require care
18 1 36 Four adults and one child in critical condition are still at San Francisco General suffering from internal bleeding fractures and spinal cord abdominal and traumatic brain injuries according to the hospital
18 1 37 Crew recall plane being too high then too low
18 1 38 The flying pilot and instructor pilot who were in the front seat of the cockpit were not among the injured according to Hersman
18 1 39 Asiana hired the flying pilot in  after which he reported amassing nearly  hours of total flight time
18 1 40 That eerience included time piloting  and A aircraft and he was a ground school and simulator instructor for the latter model
18 1 41 The instructor pilot a South Korean air force veteran with about  hours of flight eerience recalled Flight being slightly high when they passed  feet and they set vertical speed mode at about  feet per minute elained Hersman
18 1 42 But they ended up coming in low
18 1 43 The third pilot in the cockpit told investigators that with the nose  pitched up  he could not see the runway said the NTSB chief
18 1 44 In the last few hundred feet before touchdown the crew was making both lateral and vertical adjustments  meaning they were both trying to move sideways to get toward the runway and adjust their height
18 1 45 Shock and survival: Plane crash through the eyes of children
18 1 46 When the aircraft hit it spun degrees
18 1 47 An oil tank ruptured and leaked fuel onto the planes right engine starting a fire
18 1 48 Eventually evacuation chutes deployed and at least seven of the aircrafts eight doors were opened
18 1 49 An eighth was found on the ground Hersman elained
18 1 50 Very soon after the plane stopped tending to the wounded and the investigation began
18 1 51 That probe will continue for months though authorities have released significant details so far
18 1 52 So much information in fact the Air Line Pilots Association for a second straight day on Tuesday criticized what it called the NTSBs release of incomplete outofcontext information that has fueled rampant speculation about the cause of the accident
18 1 53 First responders describe eerie chaotic moments after crash
18 1 54 The union further questioned whether some tools were available to the crew claiming for instance that the Instrument Landing System a critical aid to pilots was out of service
18 1 55 Without the full body of facts surrounding a catastrophic event partial or incomplete information can lead to erroneous conclusions and in turn skew the perception of individuals behavior the pilots union said in its Tuesday statement
18 1 56 This could then lead to misguided assessments of the crews intentions and actions
18 1 57 Hersman disputed the unions claims earlier Tuesday on CNN saying the agency believes that transparent release of information is crucial
18 1 58 We believe that it is always better to put out the correct information and factual information so that bad information is not able to propagate she said
18 1 59 Aviation eerts say that air crashes often involve several factors and the San Francisco tragedy appears to be following form
18 1 60 Eerience training crew actions airport navigation and now the possible role of a mechanical system are all in the mix
18 1 61 The NTSB is not eected to render a decision on probable cause for months
18 1 62 During her news conference later Tuesday Hersman stressed that theres still a lot of work to be done
18 1 63 We will not determine probable cause while we are here on scene she said adding theres a lot of information to collect and analyze
18 1 64 I would really encourage all of you to be very cautious about speculating on the cause of the crash
18 1 65 How does an air crash investigation work?
18 1 66 CNNs Chelsea Carter Mike Ahlers and Michael Pearson contributed to this report

19 1 1 Gunman turns Batman screening into reallife horror film  CNNcom
19 1 2 The suspect in the mass shooting at an Aurora Colorado movie theater screening of the new Batman film early Friday had colored his hair red and told police he was the Joker according to a federal law enforcement source with detailed knowledge of the investigation
19 1 3 At least people were killed in the rampage and were injured one fewer than earlier reported
19 1 4 Of those injured nearly everyone was shot Aurora Police Chief Dan Oates said Friday night adding that a handful of people were hurt in the resulting chaos
19 1 5 Ten of the victims were killed inside the theater while two others died at hospitals
19 1 6 As of Friday evening the bodies had been removed from the complex and authorities were preparing to begin the agonizing process of notifying families Oates said
19 1 7 A mug shot of suspect James E Holmes has not been released
19 1 8 Witnesses to the shooting described him as wearing a gas mask that concealed much of his face and head
19 1 9 But the federal law enforcement sources information about the suspects appearance fits with a statement from New York Police Commissioner Ray Kelly who was briefed by Colorado authorities Friday
19 1 10 Oates declined to comment on Holmes appearance other than to describe what he was wearing and said he would not release his booking photo for investigative reasons
19 1 11 The Joker has long been a fixture in Batman comics and was famously brought to life by the late Heath Ledger in s The Dark Knight the predecessor to Fridays release of The Dark Knight Rises
19 1 12 Ledger won a posthumous Academy Award for his sinister portrayal of the iconic villain who encourages anarchists to take over Gotham City
19 1 13 Meanwhile authorities were faced with the difficult task of entering Holmes Aurora apartment which was left rigged with traps
19 1 14 Its boobytrapped with various incendiary and chemical devices and trip wires Oates said adding that it could take days to work through the apartment safely
19 1 15 Five buildings around the apartment building were evacuated Oates said
19 1 16 Residents were allowed back home briefly Friday night to retrieve such emergency items as medicine
19 1 17 Authorities have postponed until Saturday any attempts to enter the apartment and are bringing in resources from the federal government to help with the situation Oates said
19 1 18 Shootings cast pall over Dark Knight Rises blockbuster weekend
19 1 19 Police say Holmes  dressed headtotoe in protective tactical gear set off two devices of some kind before spraying the Century theater with bullets from an AR rifle a gauge shotgun and at least one of two caliber
19 1 20 handguns police recovered at the scene
19 1 21 Oates said the guns were purchased legally by Holmes at stores in the Denver area in the past two months
19 1 22 More than  rounds of ammunition were also purchased online according to Oates
19 1 23 A receipt obtained by CNN shows Holmes bought some of the tactical gear including a vest and magazine pouch online on July 
19 1 24 Oates said investigators are confident that Holmes acted alone
19 1 25 The shooting unfolded inside a darkened theater packed with Batman fans some in costume for the premiere of the movie
19 1 26 Aurora police said how the suspect entered the theater is still under investigation
19 1 27 A law enforcement source working the investigation told CNN that the gunman walked into the movie theater after purchasing a ticket
19 1 28 After the movie was under way he went out a rear exit door propping it open and gathered weapons before reentering through the door the source said
19 1 29 As he reentered he tossed in a canister before starting to shoot according to a second law enforcement source involved in the investigation and several witnesses
19 1 30 Screaming panicked moviegoers scrambled to escape from the blackclad gunman who shot at random as he walked up the theaters steps witnesses said
19 1 31 It was a scene straight out of a horror film said Chris Ramos who was inside the theater
19 1 32 He was just literally shooting everyone like hunting season Ramos said
19 1 33 In Aurora the agonized seek answers through faith
19 1 34 A federal law enforcement official told CNN the man used tear gas but Oates said Friday afternoon that it was not clear what the substance was
19 1 35 Holmes surrendered without resistance within seven minutes of the first calls from panicked moviegoers reporting the shooting Oates said
19 1 36 Victims flooded overwhelmed hospitals
19 1 37 One of the injured is just months old the childs mother said
19 1 38 The infant was treated and released from the hospital
19 1 39 I dont know how else to elain it
19 1 40 Its horrific said Tracy Lauzon director of EMS and trauma services at Aurora Medical Center
19 1 41 Theater shooting unfolds in real time on social media
19 1 42 Oates said the man was wearing a ballistic helmet and protective gear for his legs throat and groin black gloves and a gas mask
19 1 43 Jennifer Seeger who survived the attack said she had seen the man and thought his getup was part of the entertainment for the films debut
19 1 44 She said the man first shot toward the ceiling then began shooting at people
19 1 45 He reloaded during his attack she said
19 1 46 He was just literally just massacring anybody that got up that was trying to run away Seeger said
19 1 47 As of Friday afternoon people remained hospitalized of them in critical condition according to Colorado Gov John Hickenlooper
19 1 48 Holmes is scheduled to appear in an Arapahoe County Colorado courtroom Monday morning Rob McCallum spokesman for the Colorado Judicial Department said Friday
19 1 49 The court file was sealed according to a court order
19 1 50 He is being held in the Arapahoe County jail Oates said
19 1 51 A statement from Holmes family in San Diego asked for privacy during this difficult time

21 1 1 President shares story of hero who tended to friend in theater shooting  CNNcom
21 1 2 Seconds after a gunman shot Allie Young in the neck in a crowded Colorado theater a friend Stephanie Davies pulled her into an aisle put pressure on her wound and dialed 
21 1 3 Young told her friend to run but Davies refused
21 1 4 President Barack Obama gave that account Sunday night in Aurora praising Davies and others for heroism amid chaos and bloodshed in the shooting that killed and wounded 
21 1 5 Shooting survivors recount horror
21 1 6 The women had settled in alongside others early Friday for a midnight showing of The Dark Knight Rises the latest installment in the Batman series
21 1 7 Suddenly a gunman threw canisters only a few feet from where the pair sat
21 1 8 Young  instinctively stood to act or warn others
21 1 9 A shot ripped into her neck
21 1 10 She collapsed blood spurting from the wound Obama said
21 1 11 Instead of running or hiding Davies  pulled Young into the aisle and put pressure on the wound with one hand and dialed with the other Obama said
21 1 12 I dont know how many people at any age would have the presence of mind that Stephanie did or the courage that Allie showed the president said
21 1 13 They represent whats best in us and they assure us that out of this darkness a brighter day is going to come
21 1 14 When the SWAT team arrived Davies helped carry Young to an ambulance
21 1 15 Because of Davies actions Young is going to be fine the president said
21 1 16 Obama flew to Aurora on Sunday evening and met with families at a local hospital for more than two hours before delivering brief remarks to the media
21 1 17 Words are  inadequate Obama tells victims families

22 1 1 Colorado shooting: Stories of survival  CNNcom
22 1 2 Aurora Colorado A few reflections from survivors of the massacre at an Aurora Colorado theater from CNN interviews:
22 1 3 Thats when I felt a big ole bang in my leg
22 1 4 Bonnie Kate Pourciau  said she is not a huge Batman fan really but decided to go to the movie after she and her friend Elizabeth Sumrall stopped at a hotel in Aurora en route from Seattle to their homes in Baton Rouge Louisiana
22 1 5 When the gunfire broke out Pourciau told CNN affiliate KMGH from her bed in Aurora Medical Center she thought it was special effects in the movie
22 1 6 But she soon realized what was going on
22 1 7 Thats when I grabbed Elizabeth and we ducked under our seats
22 1 8 Crouched behind her seat she prayed
22 1 9 Lord just protect us keep us safe she recalled thinking
22 1 10 Thats when I felt a big ole bang in my leg
22 1 11 Once the shooting stopped Pourciau tried to run from the theater but didnt get far
22 1 12 Of course I fell because my knee is all gone she said about the bullet wound that shattered her knee
22 1 13 I tried to run and just stumbled and fell
22 1 14 By now Pourciau and her friend had separated in the panic and another movie patron risked his life by helping her scramble to the exit where she and Sumrall reunited she said
22 1 15 Elizabeth laid me on the concrete and a police officer and a member of the National Guard soon approached
22 1 16 The officer carried her to a patrol car and the member of the National Guard wrapped her leg which had been losing blood quickly
22 1 17 Despite the chaos Pourciau said she felt calm
22 1 18 I was overwhelmed with the sense of security and peace  that it was going to be OK she said
22 1 19 Having already undergone three surgeries on her leg Pourciau said she eected to be transferred Thursday to a hospital closer to her home
22 1 20 A silver lining to a very dark cloud
22 1 21 Baby Hugo was born Tuesday morning to Katie and Caleb Medley
22 1 22 They had gone to the movie as a treat before the eected delivery this week of their child
22 1 23 The gunfire did not strike Katie but Caleb was shot in the face
22 1 24 He lost his right eye suffered brain damage and is in critical condition
22 1 25 His brother said Caleb seems to understand what happened but it was unclear whether he knew he has a baby boy
22 1 26 Hes making small improvements baby steps every day said Seth Medley about his eldest brother
22 1 27 When the baby was taken into Calebs hospital room he moved his hand towards the baby trying to feel his son trying to touch him
22 1 28 Calebs heart rate and blood pressure rose Seth said
22 1 29 Caleb had been doing standup comedy routines in Denver and was working full time at Target but he had no health insurance his brother said
22 1 30 Seth Medley said becoming an uncle was bittersweet for him
22 1 31 We were all looking forward to this he said
22 1 32 Its a silver lining to a very dark cloud but we all know Caleb we know hes a fighter we know hes not going to stay out of that childs life for any length of time if he can avoid it
22 1 33 Christian Bale visits victims families honor lost loved ones
22 1 34 There were kids mothers and fathers
22 1 35 Josh Nowlan survived the bloodbath in Aurora and his friends hail him as a hero for shielding them with his body
22 1 36 Nowlan was shot in the left calf and right arm in the process
22 1 37 Of course Im glad its over with and Im glad Im alive and I get to see my kids Nowlan whose sons are and  said as his voice cracked with emotion
22 1 38 But I also think about you know the other people that werent as lucky as I was
22 1 39 There were kids mothers and fathers that were there and theyre dead
22 1 40 Im still alive
22 1 41 Nowlan said he wants to go back into the screening room where the killings took place look down at that same seat and say I beat you
22 1 42 You did not take this life
22 1 43 
22 1 44 Tales of heroism abound from tragedy
22 1 45 You dont want to leave knowing that you said something
22 1 46 Corbin Dates says hes not sure how he survived the killings
22 1 47 He and a friend both escaped unhurt and he said he has a blank feeling inside when he looks back at the building
22 1 48 Remembering the victims
22 1 49 But the eerience left him sounding somewhat philosophical
22 1 50 Certain circumstances can happen at any time he said
22 1 51 Try to make the most of what you can with your family your friends colleagues people that you probably had bad past relationships with
22 1 52 Because you dont want to leave knowing that you said something or didnt say enough
22 1 53 Who eects to be shot in a movie theater?
22 1 54 Christina Blache was also wounded in the early Friday massacre
22 1 55 Her friend and coworker Alex Sully Sullivan was shot in the head and Blache found out Saturday morning that he didnt survive
22 1 56 He was the whole reason we all went Blache said from her hospital bed
22 1 57 Brain condition may have helped saved shooting victim
22 1 58 Blache served in the Air Force until four years ago and her service included a stint in the Iraqi capital Baghdad
22 1 59 But at home in a moviehouse nobody was prepared for the violence that was unleashed she said
22 1 60 If youre going over to a war zone you know theres the potential that youre going to be shot at
22 1 61 Potential that mortars are going to come over the wall
22 1 62 Potential that somebody is going to throw a grenade at you
22 1 63 Where if youre sitting in a movie theater trying to watch a movie with your friends who eects to be shot in a movie theater?
22 1 64 None of us did
22 1 65 Im going to live my life a little bit better
22 1 66 Eric Hunter caught a glimpse of the killers eyes during the rampage
22 1 67 They looked pretty intense but betrayed no emotion he said
22 1 68 Like others Hunter said he thought the first three shots were a stunt part of the moviegoing eerience
22 1 69 Then he heard nine more
22 1 70 He helped two teenage girls to safety as they fled the theater
22 1 71 Surviving with the guilt of living
22 1 72 He says the killings have changed his life: Im going to be more cautious
22 1 73 Im going to live my life a little bit better and just enjoy myself
22 1 74 CNNs Don Lemon Kyung Lah and Meredith Edwards contributed to this report

23 1 1 Tales of heroism abound from Colorado movie theater tragedy  CNNcom
23 1 2 Even as a masked gunman kept firing a hailstorm of bullets in a Colorado movie theater acts of selflessness and heroism sprouted from all across the room
23 1 3 Three of the people killed died while shielding their girlfriends from the gunfire
23 1 4 And a young woman risked her life to aid her wounded friend refusing to leave her side
23 1 5 Such valor President Barack Obama said represents whats best in us and assure the country that out of this darkness a brighter day is going to come
23 1 6 Remembering the Colorado shooting victims
23 1 7 Here are some of the tales of bravery:
23 1 8 Jonathan Blunk
23 1 9 Blunk a Navy veteran was killed trying to provide cover for his girlfriend Jansen Young
23 1 10 He laid up against me and had the other side of my body against the concrete seating and I was pretty much boxed in Young said
23 1 11 He is a hero
23 1 12 And he was a hero before this and before I met him
23 1 13 All he wanted to do was serve his country and help people in need Young said
23 1 14 He used to say he was born to serve his country and he just really is
23 1 15 Hes a true hero
23 1 16 Blunk is survived by two young children
23 1 17 Blunks former wife Chantel Blunk said their yearold daughter now takes comfort in calling her fathers cell phone and hearing his voice on his voice mail message
23 1 18 One victims account: What it was like in the theater
23 1 19 Stephanie Davies  and Allie Young
23 1 20 When the gunman initially came in and threw the incendiary canisters he threw them only a few feet away from Allie and Stephanie Obama said in a speech in Aurora on Sunday shortly after meeting with the two friends
23 1 21 Allie stood up seeing that she might need to do something or at least warn the other people who were there and she was immediately shot
23 1 22 The bullet pierced a vein in Allies neck which immediately started spurting blood
23 1 23 Focusing on the victims not the shooter
23 1 24 As she dropped down on the floor Stephanie  years old  had the presence of mind to drop down on the ground with her pull her out of the aisle place her fingers over where Allie had been wounded and applied pressure the entire time while the gunman was still shooting the president said
23 1 25 Allie told Stephanie she needed to run
23 1 26 But Stephanie refused to go and instead used her other hand to call 
23 1 27 When police arrived Stephanie and several others carried Allie across two parking lots to a waiting ambulance
23 1 28 Allie is eected to recover
23 1 29 I dont know how many people at any age would have the presence of mind that Stephanie did or the courage that Allie showed Obama said
23 1 30 And so as tragic as the circumstances of what weve seen  are as heartbreaking as it is for the families its worth us spending most of our time reflecting on young Americans like Allie and Stephanie because they represent whats best in us and they assure us that out of this darkness a brighter day is going to come
23 1 31 Victims of Colorado massacre remembered with poignant stories
23 1 32 Matt McQuinn
23 1 33 McQuinn died shielding his girlfriend Samantha Yowler during the shooting family attorney Rob Scott said
23 1 34 Samantha Yowler was shot in the knee but is eected to make a full recovery Scott said
23 1 35 Her brother Nick who also was trying to protect her from the bullets also survived
23 1 36 McQuinn and Samantha Yowler grew up in the Miami Valley region of Ohio according to CNN affiliate WKEF
23 1 37 McQuinns stepfather David Jackson told CNN affiliate WHIO that the young couple was planning to move back to Springfield Ohio
23 1 38 I know hes a hero Jackson said
23 1 39 He and Sam were very much in love and planning their life together
23 1 40 I am sure they were thinking very seriously of getting married soon
23 1 41 Words are inadequate Obama tells families of Colorado shooting victims
23 1 42 Alex Teves
23 1 43 Teves was killed while protecting his girlfriend Amanda Lindgren
23 1 44 I wouldnt be here without him Lindgren said
23 1 45 Teves graduated in June with a masters degree in counseling psychology from the University of Denver where he met Lindgren
23 1 46 His best friend Ryan Cooper recalled Teves kindness
23 1 47 We love going to football and basketball games together Cooper said
23 1 48 As much as he loved that he would take time and miss those games to mentor kids in the community who didnt have dads and were just really hurting
23 1 49 Share your tribute to the victims on CNN iReport
23 1 50 CNNs Anderson Cooper contributed to this report

24 1 1 Colorado hospitals chip in for shooting victims care  CNNcom
24 1 2 With many patients still being cared for after last weeks Colorado movie theater shootings one burden is being lifted by some of the hospitals: medical eenses
24 1 3 Childrens Hospital Colorado said it will use its charity care program and donations to cover medical eenses for victims of the shooting who do not have insurance
24 1 4 Victims who do have insurance will have their copays and deductiblerelated eenses waived
24 1 5 We are committed to supporting these families as they heal Elizabeth Whitehead spokeswoman for Childrens Hospital Colorado said in a statement
24 1 6 HealthONE the healthcare system that includes the Medical Center of Aurora and Swedish Medical Center which both are treating patients from the theater shooting is also taking measures to alleviate victims costs
24 1 7 Father campaigns for more time off for grieving parents
24 1 8 The health system will eliminate personal financial responsibility for hospital charges as appropriate to each patient and the circumstances these individuals find themselves in with regard to the shooting victims according to a statement
24 1 9 Denver Health issued a statement saying that the hospital discounts bills for all patients unable to pay for copays and deductibles by  following Colorado state law
24 1 10 Each case is evaluated individually
24 1 11 Almost half of all of the hospitals patients are uninsured
24 1 12 There are more than million people in Colorado who were uninsured or underinsured as of November according to the Colorado Health Access Survey
24 1 13 This represents nearly  of people who live in the state
24 1 14 Underinsured means people have significant outofpocket medical costs despite carrying insurance
24 1 15 The mostoften reported reason for not having health insurance is high cost the survey found
24 1 16 Not having access to insurance sponsored by employers and the loss or transition of jobs were also frequently mentioned
24 1 17 Fewer employers are now providing health insurance given that the percentage of Coloradans who got insurance through work was  down from  in 
24 1 18 Those between and years old are the population group most likely to be uninsured in the state with  of them lacking insurance according to the survey
24 1 19 Many victims of the Colorado theater shooting are in this age range
24 1 20 Brain condition helps save victim
24 1 21 Some find themselves uninsured because they dont have coverage through work but others make the conscious decision to not buy insurance because they dont have any major illnesses or medical needs said Dr Ned Calonge president and CEO of the Colorado Trust which administers the health survey every other year
24 1 22 There is a bit of a gamble in saying Im young and healthy  Calonge said
24 1 23 The reality is youre just one bad day away from a major hospitalization
24 1 24 Hospitals respond to Colorado shooting
24 1 25 Legally hospitals cannot turn uninsured patients away in emergency situations so its not surprising that this would apply for Colorado shooting victims Calonge said
24 1 26 But extending additional resources for victims including those who do have insurance is philanthropic
24 1 27 It will be more of a challenge for hospitals financially if they decide to cover followup care for shooting victims since theyre not bound by law to do so and theres no obvious source of money for it he said
24 1 28 Im proud of the medical community
24 1 29 Im proud of our larger community with our response how quickly we stepped up to the plate in view of this senseless tragedy he said
24 1 30 He praised hospitals for making sure patients could be treated without worrying about whos going to pay for it
24 1 31 How to help the victims

25 1 1 Look to the good in humankind  look to heroes says grieving father  CNNcom
25 1 2 Phoenix Alex Teves treasured Marvel and DC comics with their SpiderMan and Batman icons and he was at his best in high school when he wrote about the superhero genre in English class
25 1 3 He revered the enduring themes of good versus evil and he is remembered here in the place where he grew into a man as one of the good guys: a boy who inspired an Alex Teves Day at school pursued a calling to heal both minds and bodies and died at age facing evil in the darkness of a crowded Colorado movie theater
25 1 4 If you want to describe Alex in one word he was just good says his father Tom Teves
25 1 5 He wasnt a standout in anything but he cared about people
25 1 6 It is the goodness of humanity that Teves wants the world to know and remember: the virtues of his son  and the others killed at a midnight premiere of the latest Batman movie The Dark Knight Rises in a cinema in Aurora Colorado
25 1 7 That desire has taken shape as a crusade
25 1 8 In the midst of mourning his first born Tom Teves has wrested purpose from his grief  the Alex Teves Challenge he calls it
25 1 9 He demands that the media stop naming and showing images of the gunmen in mass murders
25 1 10 Publicity glorifies killers he says and the notoriety spurs others to commit the same barbarities just for attention
25 1 11 Columbine
25 1 12 Virginia Tech
25 1 13 Tucson
25 1 14 And now Aurora
25 1 15 Alex Teves had just completed his masters degree in psychological counseling
25 1 16 His father says he would have condemned the practice of focusing on the murderers
25 1 17 Remember the victims the heroic acts Tom Teves exhorts
25 1 18 Let good triumph over evil
25 1 19 A zest for life
25 1 20 Alex Teves died shielding his girlfriend from the rain of bullets
25 1 21 His last act was more than just heroism
25 1 22 It attested to his nature to help humankind
25 1 23 Opinion: They lost their lives upheld the code
25 1 24 Fresh out of the University of Denver with his masters degree he was readying to seek another degree a bachelors in physical therapy at the University of Colorado at Boulder
25 1 25 He chose this long path because he wanted to heal the whole person his family says
25 1 26 Tom Teves is deeply satisfied that the oldest of the couples three children all sons came to know himself so well
25 1 27 He told me one day Im not going to do what you do  because its business says Teves an executive for a corporate services firm
25 1 28 Alex said he didnt have it in him to order people around
25 1 29 And it was my proudest moment
25 1 30 He knew what he wanted to do the father adds
25 1 31 Alexs mother Caren recalls his everpresent smile and appetite for life
25 1 32 He loved food
25 1 33 He loved to travel
25 1 34 He loved to elore new things
25 1 35 He just had a zest for life
25 1 36 He just wanted to eerience everything he could
25 1 37 Im glad he did as much as he could in the time he had here
25 1 38 He met his girlfriend in graduate school and Alex planned to marry her once he finished his studies the mother says
25 1 39 Tales of heroism in Aurora
25 1 40 In the elegantly designed Phoenix community of Ahwatukee where the boulevards are desertlandscaped with saguaro cacti and palo verde trees Alex was such an ordinary guy of irrepressible cheer that he was celebrated for it by his classmates at Desert Vista High School a highperforming public school opened in that sends graduates to the Ivy League
25 1 41 Every day he wore a crisp white Tshirt blue jeans and loafers to school; he just wasnt into materialism and liked to think of the more important things his mother said
25 1 42 By his senior year his AP statistics classmates  and then the entire class of  decided to hold a day in his honor
25 1 43 Everyone came to school dressed like him
25 1 44 And now says his mother friends and supporters of those slain in the movie theater massacre held a memorial service in Denver with an Alex Teves dress code and friends in Hawaii told the family they were planning a similarly attired service
25 1 45 Alex Teves was a cooperative student with a streak for being fun and funny says high school math instructor Francoise Dastous who teaches the statistics class
25 1 46 He really didnt have a clique per se
25 1 47 He got along well with everybody and everybody wanted to be friends with him
25 1 48 Alex once recounted to the class a hiking adventure that went awry Dastous says
25 1 49 For anyone else the eerience would have been horrific but Alex put a positive spin on it Dastous says
25 1 50 He was just really engaging and really fun to listen to
25 1 51 Six years have passed since the yearold teacher had Alex in class but the memories are clear
25 1 52 He just really kind of stood out from the other kids
25 1 53 He was always smiling
25 1 54 Alex was an honors student whom other faculty recalled as having a sense of humor says Anna Battle principal of the student school one of the largest in Arizona
25 1 55 He wasnt Mr Flamboyant
25 1 56 He wasnt Mr Social Anybody
25 1 57 He was an evenkeeled pleasant quality young man who loved superheroes Battle says
25 1 58 One English teacher said he was a good writer and wrote exceptionally about superheroes
25 1 59 Unfortunately it sounds like the young man who created this incident in the Colorado movie theater had some challenges that Alex may have been able to help Battle adds
25 1 60 The alleged gunman is also and was a neuroscience doctoral student at University of Colorado Anschutz Medical Campus in Aurora
25 1 61 According to a court document filed by his public defense attorneys he was also a patient of a university psychiatrist
25 1 62 My hero every day
25 1 63 Alex Teves will not be forgotten
25 1 64 His father shares one more memory
25 1 65 Alex was injured with a group of kids when their car rolled over in an accident in the desert
25 1 66 He was a student at the University of Arizona at the time
25 1 67 When an ambulance arrived Alex insisted the other passengers get inside first his father recalls even though he needed immediate treatment too
25 1 68 Once in intensive care Alex asked his father to visit one of his friends who was hospitalized because that boys parents had yet to arrive
25 1 69 Thats the kind of kid he was the father says
25 1 70 The world is worse off because hes not in it
25 1 71 Colorado shooting victims remembered for vitality selflessness
25 1 72 That the suspect had dyed his hair red to resemble the villain Joker of the Batman series is a cruel turn of fate that enrages the grieving father
25 1 73 Tom Teves doesnt want his sons legacy to be defined by a gunman
25 1 74 When the man first appeared in court last week in Colorado Teves was there
25 1 75 He calls the suspect a coward
25 1 76 He didnt look like much Teves says
25 1 77 My son could have wiped the floor with him
25 1 78 Then the father continues: If he would have known my son he would have helped him
25 1 79 He returns to his challenge to the media
25 1 80 He blames news outlets including CNN for playing a role in perpetuating mass shootings
25 1 81 You make him out to be a madman he says of the man suspected of killing his son
25 1 82 He knew he was going to be on television
25 1 83 These guys are playing you like fiddles
25 1 84 Either youre not that bright  I used a better word than I was thinking of  or you dont care and youre using it to sell advertising and then youre the worst thing on the face of the earth
25 1 85 Tom and Caren Teves have been married years
25 1 86 He worked two or three jobs sometimes so that their kids could benefit from having their mother at home fulltime
25 1 87 Now the couple faces raising their  and yearold sons without their big brother
25 1 88 He was my hero every day Teves says
25 1 89 The father isnt surprised by the way Alex responded when savagery slipped inside the movie theater
25 1 90 Alex is in heaven he adds
25 1 91 Im quite sure of it
25 1 92 His anger subsides
25 1 93 The couple is accompanied by Caren Teves sister and her husband whom the Teveses earlier picked up at the Phoenix airport
25 1 94 The inlaws Joe and Carla Morgan eress outrage that the suspects photo appears five times on the front page of a national newspaper overwhelming any photos of Alex and the others who lost their lives
25 1 95 Stop showing cowards and start showing heroes Tom Teves says so that another father doesnt feel the hole in his body that I have and I know will never go away
25 1 96 He puts his hand over his heart
25 1 97 His wife extends her hand and joins his
25 1 98 Its got to end he says
25 1 99 You do your part and I promise to do the other
25 1 100 He says he will spend his days reminding the media of this challenge in his sons name

26 1 0 
26 1 1 Looking into the minds of killers  CNNcom
26 1 2 Editors note: Jeffrey Swanson is a professor in psychiatry and behavioral sciences at Duke Universitys School of Medicine
26 1 3 A witness to the horrific shooting rampage in the Colorado movie theater called it the longest minute of his life
26 1 4 One can only imagine
26 1 5 But the second longest minute may be the waiting for someone  the authorities the pundits the doctors  to tell us why these killings happened
26 1 6 Police say James Holmes a yearold graduate student in a neurosciences program called himself the Joker and rained merciless bullets on strangers watching a Batman movie
26 1 7 Why?
26 1 8 Colorado theater shooting suspect makes first court appearance
26 1 9 Already the speculations are flooding in
26 1 10 Theres a celebrity psychiatrist saying it was a failure of empathy likely rooted in the shooters early life psychological pain
26 1 11 What about asking the accused shooters parents?
26 1 12 Listen these folks that are now flying to join their son in Colorado if you were to ask them What three things are you most sensitive about not telling people about your family or your sons personal development or the things that are most painful to relate  theres your answer
26 1 13 Another psychiatrist thinks that people who commit crimes like this are unfailingly unable to form satisfying sexual attachments and their masculinity essentially gets replaced with their fascination for destruction
26 1 14 Big Religion has also weighed in
26 1 15 The product of pure evil  a depraved individual taking his free will to the extreme says the president of Focus on the Family
26 1 16 The head of the Southern Baptists commented that the incident tells the truth about unbridled human sin
26 1 17 They should all shut up
26 1 18 Let the police work
26 1 19 Let a competent clinician conduct a private evaluation
26 1 20 Let the professional reporters find out what really happened
26 1 21 Former colleague shocked that Holmes is theater shooting suspect
26 1 22 On the face of it a deliberate rampage to kill strangers is the act of a deviant consciousness of some kind
26 1 23 But we dont know whether the accused killers mind may have been driven by acute symptoms of a psychiatric disorder that impairs thought and perception of reality by a personality misshaped through a troubled past or by something else entirely
26 1 24 We simply dont know
26 1 25 What we do know based on the best available scientific evidence on the link between violence and mental illness in populations is that most violence is not caused by a major psychiatric condition like schizophrenia bipolar disorder or depression
26 1 26 Psychiatric disorder accounts for only about  of violent behavior across the spectrum from minor to serious assaultive acts
26 1 27 And the vast majority of people with serious mental illnesses do not behave violently
26 1 28 If research on patterns of violence in populations tells us anything its that no single thing causes assaultive behavior
26 1 29 Even when serious psychopathology plays a role it is almost never a sufficient elanation
26 1 30 Other variables  personal background characteristics and life eerience features of the social environment substance abuse  all may interact to make violent acts statistically more likely
26 1 31 That makes it complicated to elain and very difficult to predict actions on an individual level
26 1 32 Court appearance fuels theories about Colorado shooting suspect
26 1 33 After the fact rare and appalling acts of violence somehow look predictable and thus preventable
26 1 34 It is natural to turn to the eerts but they always come up short
26 1 35 They are notoriously bad at forecasting even garden variety violence to say nothing of finding the oneinamillion wouldbe mass shooter
26 1 36 When we total up the contributions of all the risk factors with known links to violent behavior most of it is left unelained
26 1 37 When we describe the common characteristics of mass shooters were left with a profile that fits tens of thousands of troubled young men who would never actually do such a senseless thing
26 1 38 Is Holmes a psychopath?
26 1 39 The true reasons that motivated the terrible act of which he is accused may always remain obscure
26 1 40 But what should not be obscure is how easy it is for troubled young men legally to acquire a small arsenal of firearms in the United States
26 1 41 If Holmes hadnt been able to get his hands on the guns police say he used this would be a different story 
26 1 42 Opinion: Mass murder and powerful firearms
26 1 43 People can disagree about whether million firearms in private hands in the country is too many guns
26 1 44 But they should not disagree that  people dying from gunshots in the past decade is too many wasted lives
26 1 45 The notion of forbidding assault weapons and largecapacity ammunition magazines  machines specifically designed to kill multiple people in the twinkling of an eye  is not about infringing the Second Amendment
26 1 46 It is about common sense and protecting the public
26 1 47 Such weapons were successfully legally banned in the United States from to ; they should be banned again
26 1 48 Still dangerous guns per se are not the only problem and banning them is only part of the solution
26 1 49 We also need better means of identifying dangerous people who should not have access to guns
26 1 50 Research shows that one of the highest risk times for violence in people who develop a psychotic illness is their first episode  the period right before they establish any record with the formal mental health care system
26 1 51 Gun laws such as the federal Brady Act that are implemented through background record searches wont find these individuals
26 1 52 But even having a formal record of involuntary psychiatric hospitalization is no guarantee that the relevant information will be available at the point of purchase of a firearm
26 1 53 Opinion: When will America wake up to gun violence?
26 1 54 In Colorado only a tiny fraction about  of people who have gundisqualifying mental health histories have been reported to the National Instant Check System where they could be discovered in a routine background check of a prospective gun purchaser
26 1 55 A felony conviction is also supposed to disqualify people from buying a gun but only  of murder suspects have such a previous record of conviction
26 1 56 The present national moment of grief and soul searching should not become another occasion for oversimplifying the problem of gun violence and laying the blame on any one thing  its the guns or its untreated mental illness or its the information system or its the violent popular culture in society
26 1 57 It may be all of those things
26 1 58 We need to address all of the variables and come up with smart evidencebased policies
26 1 59 Looking inside the killers head should not be the first place to start
26 1 60 Follow us on Twitter
26 1 61 Join us on FacebookCNNOpinion
26 1 62 The opinions eressed in this commentary are solely those of Jeffrey Swanson

27 1 4 Almost all of the victims were young  including a yearold girl who had just learned to swim
27 1 5 The cause of death in all cases is related to gunshot wounds according to the Arapahoe County Coroners Office

27 1 7 Jonathan T Blunk
27 1 8 Blunk served for five years in the US Navy
27 1 9 He had been planning to fly Saturday to Reno Nevada to see his wife Chantel his yearold daughter and his yearold son
27 1 10 We were going to have a family day Chantel Blunk said
27 1 11 Instead she put away the dress her daughter had picked out to wear to the airport
27 1 12 I tried to tell her we wouldnt see Daddy anymore but that he would still love us and look over us
27 1 13 The couple married in and separated in  she said
27 1 14 They remained on good terms after Jonathan moved to Colorado
27 1 15 Blunk died shielding his girlfriend from the gunfire inside the theater
27 1 16 Chantel Blunk said she wants her husband to have a military funeral
27 1 17 She said she will remember Jonathans humor spontaneity and attention to family
27 1 18 We love him and he is going to be remembered as a hero she said
27 1 19 Video: Blunk was a hero
27 1 20 Alexander J Boik
27 1 21 A Facebook page was created in memory of Boik a Gateway High School student who was at the theater with his girlfriend and a friend
27 1 22 AJ was an awesome kid and a truly Inspirational teammate one Facebook entry said
27 1 23 You cant find someone with a brighter smile and more positive outlook on life
27 1 24 There to help you up when your down and One to carry on life with such an intelligence
27 1 25 Boik was an independent distributor for Organo Gold a coffee company and lived in Aurora according to what appears to be his personal Facebook page
27 1 26 James Crofter father of Jordan Crofter Boiks friend who survived the shooting said Jordan and Boik played lacrosse together
27 1 27 Boiks girlfriend also was in the theater
27 1 28 She and Jordan found each other outside the theater but Boik did not make it out

27 1 30 Air Force Staff Sgt
27 1 31 Jesse E Childress
27 1 32 Childress an Air Force reservist was a cybersystems operator on active duty with the th Force Support Squadron at Buckley Air Force Base in Colorado
27 1 33 He was from Thornton Colorado
27 1 34 Jesse was an invaluable part of the th family said Lt Col Pat Walsh who was Childress supervisor according to The Washington Post
27 1 35 He literally touched everyone in the wing  over  people
27 1 36 Three of Childress Air Force colleagues traveled from Buckley to honor him at a memorial near the theater The Denver Post reported
27 1 37 He was a huge part of our unit and this is a terrible loss

27 1 39 She declined to give her first name
27 1 40 Gordon W Cowden
27 1 41 Cowden took his two teenage children to the theater
27 1 42 His children escaped unharmed according to Californias Ventura County Star
27 1 43 A family spokesman described Cowden as a loving father outdoorsman and smallbusiness owner according to the Star
27 1 44 Cowden was a true Texas gentleman that loved life and his family
27 1 45 A quickwitted world traveler with a keen sense of humor he will be remembered for his devotion to his children and for always trying his best to do the right thing no matter the obstacle
27 1 46 Focusing on the victims not the shooter
27 1 47 Jessica Ghawi
27 1 48 Aspiring sports reporter Ghawi narrowly avoided a shooting in Toronto just last month  an incident that prompted her to reflect on life on her blog
27 1 49 The Toronto shooting at the Eaton Centre left one person dead and seven wounded
27 1 50 I was shown how fragile life was on Saturday
27 1 51 I saw the terror on bystanders faces
27 1 52 I saw the victims of a senseless crime
27 1 53 I saw lives change she wrote at the time
27 1 54 I was reminded that we dont know when or where our time on Earth will end
27 1 55 When or where we will breathe our last breath
27 1 56 Ghawi who also went by the name Jessica Redfield grew up in Texas and interned at Ticket  a sports radio station in San Antonio before moving to Denver to try to break into the television market there
27 1 57 A memorial service is scheduled for July in San Antonio
27 1 58 Brother: Ghawi an aspiring sports writer

27 1 60 Like his father and grandfather Larimer chose to join the US Navy
27 1 61 He was serving at his first post said his father Scott Larimer

27 1 70 He had not seen combat

27 1 96 Veronica MoserSullivan
27 1 97 Thirteenyearold Kaylan was Veronicas babysitter and she was seated with the girl and Veronicas mother when the shooting began
27 1 98 He just kept firing and then he would stop like he was reloading and he kept firing at anyone he saw Kaylan told CNNs Poppy Harlow
27 1 99 Kaylan watched as three people with her were shot  Veronica the girls mother Ashley Moser and their pastor Michael Walker
27 1 100 I felt like it was partly my job to protect her and even if I wasnt her babysitter I would still feel that same because she was just a child she said
27 1 101 Lying on the theater floor she called  then put her hand on Veronicas ribcage to see if she was breathing
27 1 102 But she wasnt breathing so I started freaking out and then they told me to do CPR and I told them I couldnt because her mother was on top of her and couldnt move
27 1 103 Described as a vibrant little girl Veronica  an only child  had just learned to swim and was excited about life her greataunt said

27 1 128 Wingo joined the Air Force after high school became fluent in Mandarin and served as a translator according to CNN DallasFort Worth affiliate WFAA

28 1 42  His immediate response was to protect the one that he loved
28 1 43 Alex Teves  also died while protecting his girlfriend Amanda Lindgren
28 1 44 More than a week later his friends and family gathered in Phoenix to remember his spirit and life
28 1 45 Attendees including Teves parents attended the memorial service in white Tshirts and blue jeans just as Teves routinely did while in high school and beyond
28 1 46 Teves graduated in June with a masters degree in counseling psychology from the University of Denver
28 1 47 He wasnt very vain he was more interested in relationships his father Tom Teves told reporters Saturday before entering Corpus Christi Catholic Church for the service
28 1 48 
28 1 49 He put people first always
28 1 50 About  miles away in Crystal Lake Illinois Larimer received full military honors at his funeral
28 1 51 The Navy petty officer rd class had been in the military for about one year
28 1 52 Like his father and grandfather the yearold Larimer chose to join the US Navy
28 1 53 He was serving at his first post said his father Scott Larimer
28 1 54 Meanwhile a court document filed Friday showed suspect James Holmes was a patient of a University of Colorado psychiatrist before last weeks attack at a movie theater that killed people and wounded scores
28 1 55 The disclosure was in a request by Holmes for authorities to immediately hand over a package he sent to Dr Lynne Fenton at the universitys Anschutz Medical Campus
28 1 56 According to Holmes request the package seized by authorities under a July search warrant was a protected communication
28 1 57 The materials contained in that package include communications from Mr Holmes to Dr Fenton that Mr Holmes asserts are privileged said the document filed by public defenders representing Holmes
28 1 58 Mr
28 1 59 Holmes was a psychiatric patient of Dr Fenton and his communications with her are protected
28 1 60 Victims remembered with poignant stories
28 1 61 In response prosecutors asked for Arapahoe County District Judge William Sylvester to deny the request by Holmes saying it contained inaccuracies including claims of media leaks by government officials that in reality may have been fabricated by news organizations
28 1 62 Sylvester granted a hearing on the request for Monday the same day that Holmes is scheduled to be formally charged in the case
28 1 63 Eleven wounded survivors remained hospitalized Saturday at three facilities including five in critical condition
28 1 64 One of them Ashley Moser underwent an additional surgery on Saturday morning and also suffered a miscarriage due to the extreme trauma she sustained her family said in a statement
28 1 65 Mosers yearold daughter Veronica was the youngest person killed in the shooting

29 1 1 Theater shooting unfolds in real time on social media  CNNcom
29 1 2 The posts show how quickly life can change
29 1 3 Everyones dressing up as Batman im going dressed as Bruce Wayne Albeit a short stubby unsexy Bruce Wayne  wrote one Twitter user identified online as Zach Eastman
29 1 4 Going to see the final batman tonight
29 1 5 So EXCITED wrote another Twitter user 
29 1 6 And in hindsight most chillingly: Of course were seeing Dark Knight  people should never argue with me
29 1 7 Gunman kills in Colorado theater shooting
29 1 8 Those posts surfaced before the shootings early Friday morning at a latenight showing in Aurora Colorado of the Batman movie The Dark Knight Rises in which people were killed and dozens more were injured
29 1 9 All three people who were quoted above appear to have been in the theater complex when a heavily armed gunman opened fire on moviegoers according to police
29 1 10 The third post appears to be from Jessica Ghawi who was reported dead in the shooting
29 1 11 Ghawi was a former sportsnews intern at a television station in San Antonio according to that station Fox 
29 1 12 Its true my former intern Jessica Ghawi was a victim in the shootings last night
29 1 13 She used as her twitter handle wrote a Twitter user identified as Mike Taylor
29 1 14 In the hours after the shooting her friend mourned her death in real time
29 1 15 Devastated wrote a sports radio host in Denver identified online as Peter Burns
29 1 16 Lost a very close friend in the shooting last night
29 1 17 came to Denver to pursue sports career
29 1 18 Im shaking
29 1 19 Aspiring sports reporter Ghawi feared dead in shooting
29 1 20 The horrifying posts highlight a shift in the way our society tells the story of a tragedy and also how we react to it
29 1 21 Before Twitter smartphones and YouTube it would have been impossible for an event like Colorados Batman Massacre to have played out for the global public in real time
29 1 22 The shooting is just the latest instance of social media being used to document a tragedy or a news event even as it is unfolding
29 1 23 A Pakistani man last year unwittingly livetweeted the raid that killed Osama bin Laden
29 1 24 And the war in Syria is being documented in large part by citizens and members of the opposition movement who risk their lives to post YouTube videos and photos of the violence
29 1 25 NRA tweeter was unaware of Colorado shooting spokesman says
29 1 26 But the social media posts about the Colorado shooting are a haunting reminder of the visceral power of firstperson accounts of tragedy
29 1 27 And also a sign that society these days deals with grieving after an event like this in a much more public and immediate way than in years past
29 1 28 Reports of the Columbine school shooting for example which happened only miles from Aurora spread in a much different way
29 1 29 Thirteen years ago witnesses talked to TV crews rather than uploading their stories instantly to the Internet with mobile phones

30 1 1 Colorado shooting suspect was a psychiatric patient  CNNcom
30 1 2 Colorado shooting suspect James Holmes was a patient of a University of Colorado psychiatrist before last weeks attack at a movie theater that killed people and wounded scores according to a court document filed Friday by his publicdefense lawyers
30 1 3 The disclosure was in a request by Holmes for authorities to immediately hand over a package he sent to Dr Lynne Fenton at the universitys Anschutz Medical Campus
30 1 4 According to Holmes request the package seized by authorities under a July search warrant was a protected communication
30 1 5 The materials contained in that package include communications from Mr Holmes to Dr Fenton that Mr Holmes asserts are privileged said the document filed by public defenders representing Holmes
30 1 6 Mr
30 1 7 Holmes was a psychiatric patient of Dr Fenton and his communications with her are protected
30 1 8 In response prosecutors asked for Arapahoe County District Judge William Sylvester to deny the request by Holmes saying it contained inaccuracies including claims of media leaks by government officials that in reality may have been fabricated by news organizations
30 1 9 Sylvester granted a hearing on the request for Monday the same day that Holmes is scheduled to be formally charged in the case
30 1 10 Court appearance fuels theories about Colorado shooting suspect
30 1 11 Meanwhile wounded survivors remained hospitalized Friday at three facilities including five in critical condition
30 1 12 At Swedish Medical Center two victims were in fair condition after multiple surgeries since the shootings a hospital spokeswoman said
30 1 13 Both appear to be doing well and their spirits are definitely at a higher level said Audra Mincey public relations manager at the medical center
30 1 14 Holmes allegedly opened fire in the theater on July during the midnight premiere of the Batman movie The Dark Knight Rises
30 1 15 The suspect  who identified himself to police as the Joker remained in custody after being ordered held without bond earlier this week and will be formally charged on Monday
30 1 16 A group of media organizations including CNN asked Sylvester on Friday to unseal court documents in the case particularly affidavits for probable cause involving search warrants that already have been executed
30 1 17 Two court orders posted on a court website Thursday noted restrictions on information the University of Colorado could release about Holmes
30 1 18 The yearold had recently dropped out of a PhD program in neuroscience out of the schools campus in Aurora
30 1 19 The orders in addition to a previous one issued Wednesday aimed at limiting pretrial publicity at the defendants request endeavor to restrict the amount of publicly available information in order to assure the fairness of a trial
30 1 20 Authorities discovered the package Holmes sent Fenton on Monday in a mailroom at the University of Colorado  Anschutz Medical Campus a law enforcement official briefed on the investigation said Wednesday
30 1 21 CBS News reported that according to unidentified sources the letter was from a pentup Holmes to one of his professors
30 1 22 In it he talked about shooting people and even included crude drawings of a gunman and his victims according to the CBS report
30 1 23 In the court request for authorities to turn over the package Holmes cited media leaks as a violation of Sylvesters court orders
30 1 24 Prosecutors responded that there was no proof that government officials leaked any information and said the reported leaks may well have been fabricated by news organizations
30 1 25 To put it bluntly the People are extremely dubious of the media assertions that law enforcement sources exist said the prosecution document
30 1 26 University spokeswoman Jacque Montgomery said Friday the university had no further comment at the moment
30 1 27 Holmes had boobytrapped his sparsely furnished thirdfloor onebedroom unit apartment with more than homemade grenades and gallons of gasoline a law enforcement official who viewed video showing the apartments interior has told CNN
30 1 28 The sophisticated setup was meant to harm or possibly kill anyone who entered  and tested the skills of bomb squad members charged with clearing it the official said
30 1 29 Other tenants of the apartment building where Holmes had lived were rousted out of their apartments by police in the early hours of July after the shooting
30 1 30 They were allowed to begin returning home more than five days later
30 1 31 Official: Trap in Colorado suspects home had homemade grenades gasoline
30 1 32 Some of the shooting victims both in and out of hospitals faced a difficult recovery process and the prospect of daunting medical bills
30 1 33 They include Caleb Medley who lost an eye and suffered brain damage
30 1 34 His wife gave birth to their son Hugo Jackson Medley on Tuesday morning and the University of Colorado Hospital said both baby and mother are doing well
30 1 35 Medley who had been doing standup comedy routines in Denver and was working fulltime at Target had no health insurance his brother Seth said
30 1 36 The surgeon came and talked to us and said hed be in ICU at least a week said Medleys friend Michael West who set up a website to help take care of medical bills and the needs of Medleys family
30 1 37 By Thursday evening it had raised more than
