31 1 1 Colorado movie shooting suspect charged with murder  CNNcom
31 1 2 Centennial Colorado Colorado movie shooting suspect James Holmes was charged Monday with counts of firstdegree murder  two counts for each of the people killed in the shooting
31 1 3 Twelve of the murder counts cite deliberation and cite extreme indifference to the value of human life
31 1 4 The yearold former doctoral student also was charged with counts of attempted murder  two for each of the moviegoers wounded in the attack
31 1 5 Finally he was charged with one count of felony possession of elosive devices and one count related to the use of an assault weapon a shotgun and a handgun during the incident
31 1 6 The counts are all in connection with the July massacre in the Century Aurora multiplex minutes into a midnight screening of The Dark Knight Rises
31 1 7 Shackled around his wrists and ankles Holmes was escorted into Arapahoe County Courthouse by two sheriffs deputies
31 1 8 Five other sheriffs deputies were standing in the courtroom
31 1 9 Court appearance fuels theories about Colorado shooting suspect
31 1 10 In his first court appearance last week Holmes appeared dazed and did not speak
31 1 11 During Mondays hearing meanwhile he seemed calm and frail sitting at the right edge of the defense table with his dyedorange hair matted on top its roots dark
31 1 12 For a while he stared blankly at the judges bench but appeared to be aware of what was going on
31 1 13 When the judge asked him whether he understood why his attorneys were asking for more time before a hearing he said softly Yes
31 1 14 About half of the approximately seats in the courtroom were filled with victims or their family members; more watched on video in an overflow room
31 1 15 One young man in the front row of the courtroom leaned forward and stared at Holmes without averting his gaze throughout the minute proceeding
31 1 16 Read the charges PDF
31 1 17 Another observer her left arm and leg in bandages sat slumped in her seat
31 1 18 Around her wrist was a hospital wristband
31 1 19 It was very important to come today to see him as who he was MaryEllen Hansen told reporters outside the courthouse
31 1 20 I really wanted an opportunity to watch his gestures and study him as much as I could
31 1 21 Her nieces yearold daughter Veronica MoserSullivan was the youngest person killed in the rampage
31 1 22 Hansens niece Ashley Moser faces a long recovery after being paralyzed in her lower half and miscarrying after the shooting
31 1 23 I got a sense that he was very aware of what was going on Hansen said of Holmes
31 1 24 He had an eression and kind of a persona of evilness to him
31 1 25 But he looked very sane to me he really did

31 1 27 Background of suspect full of contrasts
31 1 28 Arapahoe County District Attorney Carol Chambers said last Monday that it will take time for prosecutors to decide whether or not they will pursue the death penalty since theyd first want to get input from victims and their relatives
31 1 29 Authorities have remained silent about a possible motive in the case
31 1 30 A court document filed Friday revealed that Holmes was a patient of a University of Colorado psychiatrist before the attack
31 1 31 The disclosure was made in a filing by Holmes public defenders requesting that authorities hand over a package he sent to Dr Lynne Fenton at the universitys Anschutz Medical Campus where he had been studying neuroscience before announcing earlier this month that he was withdrawing from the program
31 1 32 The package seized by authorities under a July search warrant should remain confidential protected by the doctorpatient relationship because Holmes was a psychiatric patient of Fenton the request said
31 1 33 In response prosecutors asked Arapahoe County District Judge William Sylvester to deny Holmes request saying it contained inaccuracies including claims of media leaks by government officials that in reality may have been fabricated by news organizations
31 1 34 The package is eected to be the focus of a status hearing set for August 
31 1 35 Prosecutors say they will begin turning over thousands of pages of discovery in the next couple of days
31 1 36 The defense says they need this information to prepare for the hearing
31 1 37 Warning signs of violence: What to do
31 1 38 During the week of November  attorneys eect a preliminary hearing and an evidence hearing that will include several days of testimony
31 1 39 As Mondays hearing unfolded survivors remained hospitalized three of them in critical condition
31 1 40 But there was some progress: The day began at the University of Colorado Hospital at Aurora for instance with three in critical one in serious and one in fair condition and ended with two in critical and three in fair condition
31 1 41 Meanwhile those affected continued to come to grips with the horror
31 1 42 On Saturday alone memorial services were held for four people killed in the massacre including two men  Matt McQuinn from Ohio and Alex Teves from Arizona  who died shielding their girlfriends from gunfire
31 1 43 Closer to Aurora which is just east of Denver people worked to make sense of what happened and support one another

32 1 0 
32 1 1 Analysis: Why gun controls are off the agenda in America  CNNcom
32 1 2 What is it about Americans and guns?
32 1 3 How much time do you have?
32 1 4 I can tell you that I dont think theres any other developed country in the world that has remotely the problem we have New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg said after the shooting rampage in Colorado
32 1 5 There are an estimated million guns in the hands of civilians in the United States making Americans the most heavily armed people in the world per capita
32 1 6 Yemen a tribal nation with no history of strong central government or the rule of law comes in a distant second
32 1 7 From Washington to the wellstocked shelves of Walmart stores nationwide guns are regarded in the United States as a commonplace if controversial consumer item for millions of lawabiding hunters collectors and citizens concerned about their safety
32 1 8 They are also in the hands of thousands of killers too; a Washingtonbased antigun lobby says those guns shoot more than  people a year
32 1 9 In  there were more than  deaths caused by firearms when the number of homicides suicides and accidental deaths are tallied
32 1 10 Read: Why has Obama largely steered clear of gun debate?
32 1 11 Americas collective memory  of the Wild West in the s the assassinations of John F Kennedy and Martin Luther King half a century ago and the frontpage news from last week  is marked time and time again by guns
32 1 12 Its undeniable writes Clayton Cramer author of Armed America: the Remarkable Story of How and Why Guns Became as American as Apple Pie Guns are at the center of much of Americas history its legends and its horrors
32 1 13 There were guns in America long before the America we know today was even born
32 1 14 Early settlers in several states were required by law to own and maintain weapons as a matter of collective defense
32 1 15 By the time the United States was established its citizens had taken up arms not only against their Native American neighbors but the army of their own king
32 1 16 Their new constitution reflected that in its Bill of Rights declaring that A well regulated militia being necessary to the security of a free state the right of the people to keep and bear arms shall not be infringed
32 1 17 For more than two centuries that remained an important but largely overlooked guarantee subjected to a modest series of controls
32 1 18 But in and  landmark Supreme Court rulings gave that constitutional right sweeping new power dramatically diminishing the authority of state and local governments to limit gun ownership
32 1 19 Gunfriendly lawmakers have been active too
32 1 20 Roughly half of the US states have adopted laws allowing gun owners to carry their guns openly in most public places
32 1 21 About as many states have stand your ground laws that allow people to kill if they come under threat even in some cases if they can escape the threat without violence
32 1 22 The laws are being driven by politics and the politics are being driven by groups such as the National Rifle Association
32 1 23 Once a relatively modest organization of gun enthusiasts and hunters it has become one of the most powerful political groups in the country
32 1 24 The Washington Post estimates that the NRA succeeded in helping elect four out of every five candidates it endorsed in the most recent congressional election
32 1 25 In addition to that extraordinary impact in Congress it has been working to overturn guncontrol laws in the courts
32 1 26 The NRA and other gunrights groups have allied themselves with the Republican Party and especially a sector of the American public suspicious of government intrusions into private life and often flatly hostile to Washington
